{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":142,"text":"So I'm a doctor, but I kind of slipped\nsideways into research,"},{"time":3230,"text":"and now I'm an epidemiologist."},{"time":4952,"text":"And nobody really knows\nwhat epidemiology is."},{"time":7120,"text":"Epidemiology is the science\nof how we know in the real world"},{"time":10297,"text":"if something is good\nfor you or bad for you."},{"time":12431,"text":"And it's best understood through example"},{"time":14415,"text":"as the science of those crazy,\nwacky newspaper headlines."},{"time":19090,"text":"And these are just some of the examples."}]},{"cues":[{"time":21447,"text":"These are from the Daily Mail."},{"time":22921,"text":"Every country in the world\nhas a newspaper like this."},{"time":25464,"text":"It has this bizarre,\nongoing philosophical project"},{"time":27838,"text":"of dividing all the inanimate\nobjects in the world"},{"time":30217,"text":"into the ones that either cause\nor prevent cancer."},{"time":32594,"text":"Here are some of the things\nthey said cause cancer:"},{"time":35126,"text":"divorce, Wi-Fi, toiletries and coffee."},{"time":37131,"text":"Some things they say prevent cancer:"},{"time":38919,"text":"crusts, red pepper, licorice and coffee."},{"time":40865,"text":"So you can see there are contradictions."},{"time":42795,"text":"Coffee both causes and prevents cancer."},{"time":44819,"text":"As you start to read on, you can see"},{"time":46567,"text":"that maybe there's some\npolitical valence behind some of this."},{"time":49530,"text":"For women, housework\nprevents breast cancer,"},{"time":51615,"text":"but for men, shopping\ncould make you impotent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":54684,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":55717,"text":"So we know that we need to start\nunpicking the science behind this."},{"time":60245,"text":"And what I hope to show is that unpicking\nthe evidence behind dodgy claims"},{"time":65802,"text":"isn't a kind of nasty, carping activity;"},{"time":69546,"text":"it's socially useful."},{"time":70931,"text":"But it's also an extremely valuable\nexplanatory tool,"},{"time":75513,"text":"because real science is about\ncritically appraising the evidence"},{"time":78572,"text":"for somebody else's position."},{"time":79989,"text":"That's what happens in academic journals,"},{"time":81972,"text":"it's what happens\nat academic conferences --"},{"time":84060,"text":"the Q&amp;A session after a postdoc\npresents data is often a bloodbath."},{"time":87393,"text":"And nobody minds that;\nwe actively welcome it."},{"time":89575,"text":"It's like a consenting\nintellectual S&amp;M activity."}]},{"cues":[{"time":92637,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":93816,"text":"So what I'm going to show you\nis all of the main things,"},{"time":96834,"text":"all of the main features of my discipline,\nevidence-based medicine."},{"time":100048,"text":"And I will talk you through all of these\nand demonstrate how they work,"},{"time":103955,"text":"exclusively using examples\nof people getting stuff wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":107321,"text":"We'll start with the absolute weakest\nform of evidence known to man,"},{"time":111099,"text":"and that is authority."},{"time":112749,"text":"In science, we don't care how many letters\nyou have after your name --"},{"time":116213,"text":"we want to know what your reasons are\nfor believing something."},{"time":119249,"text":"How do you know that something\nis good for us or bad for us?"},{"time":122269,"text":"But we're also unimpressed by authority\nbecause it's so easy to contrive."},{"time":126474,"text":"This is somebody called\nDr. Gillian McKeith, PhD,"},{"time":128880,"text":"or, to give her full\nmedical title, Gillian McKeith."}]},{"cues":[{"time":132073,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":134757,"text":"Again, every country\nhas somebody like this."},{"time":136937,"text":"She is our TV diet guru."},{"time":138605,"text":"She has five series\nof prime-time television,"},{"time":141536,"text":"giving out very lavish\nand exotic health advice."},{"time":143878,"text":"She, it turns out, has a non-accredited\ncorrespondence course PhD"},{"time":147757,"text":"from somewhere in America."},{"time":149061,"text":"She also boasts that she's a certified\nprofessional member"},{"time":151850,"text":"of the American Association\nof Nutritional Consultants,"},{"time":154466,"text":"which sounds very glamorous;\nyou get a certificate."},{"time":156889,"text":"This one belongs to my dead cat, Hettie.\nShe was a horrible cat."},{"time":159930,"text":"You go to the website, fill out the form,"},{"time":161918,"text":"give them $60, it arrives in the post."},{"time":163763,"text":"That's not the only reason\nwe think this person is an idiot."},{"time":166620,"text":"She also says things like\neat lots of dark green leaves,"},{"time":169293,"text":"they contain chlorophyll\nand really oxygenate your blood."},{"time":172174,"text":"And anybody who's done\nschool biology remembers"},{"time":174397,"text":"that chlorophyll and chloroplasts\nonly make oxygen in sunlight,"},{"time":177633,"text":"and it's quite dark in your bowels\nafter you've eaten spinach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180787,"text":"Next, we need proper science,\nproper evidence."},{"time":183310,"text":"So: \"Red wine can help\nprevent breast cancer.\""},{"time":185776,"text":"This is a headline\nfrom The Daily Telegraph in the UK."},{"time":188363,"text":"\"A glass of red wine a day could help\nprevent breast cancer.\""},{"time":191305,"text":"So you find this paper, and find\nthat it is a real piece of science."},{"time":194565,"text":"It's a description of the changes\nin the behavior of one enzyme"},{"time":197586,"text":"when you drip a chemical\nextracted from some red grape skin"},{"time":200779,"text":"onto some cancer cells"},{"time":202378,"text":"in a dish on a bench\nin a laboratory somewhere."},{"time":205602,"text":"And that's a really useful thing\nto describe in a scientific paper."},{"time":209718,"text":"But on the question of your own personal\nrisk of getting breast cancer"},{"time":213100,"text":"if you drink red wine,"},{"time":214275,"text":"it tells you absolutely bugger all."},{"time":215980,"text":"Actually, it turns out\nthat your risk of breast cancer"},{"time":218541,"text":"increases slightly with every amount\nof alcohol you drink."},{"time":221528,"text":"So what we want are studies\nin real human people."}]},{"cues":[{"time":225400,"text":"And here's another example."},{"time":227000,"text":"This is from Britain's \"leading\"\ndiet nutritionist in the Daily Mirror,"},{"time":231185,"text":"our second-biggest selling newspaper."},{"time":232983,"text":"\"An Australian study in 2001\nfound that olive oil,"},{"time":235365,"text":"in combination with fruits,\nvegetables and pulses,"},{"time":237731,"text":"offers measurable protection\nagainst skin wrinklings,\""},{"time":240303,"text":"and give the advice:"},{"time":241478,"text":"\"If you eat olive oil and vegetables,\nyou'll have fewer wrinkles.\""},{"time":244632,"text":"They helpfully tell you\nhow to find the paper,"},{"time":246814,"text":"and what you find\nis an observational study."},{"time":248925,"text":"Obviously, nobody has been able\nto go back to 1930,"},{"time":251870,"text":"get all the people born\nin one maternity unit,"},{"time":254387,"text":"and half of them eat lots\nof fruit and veg and olive oil,"},{"time":257107,"text":"half of them eat McDonald's,"},{"time":258477,"text":"and then we see how many wrinkles\nyou've got later."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260904,"text":"You have to take a snapshot\nof how people are now."},{"time":263341,"text":"And what you find is, of course:"},{"time":264929,"text":"people who eat veg and olive oil\nhave fewer wrinkles."},{"time":267454,"text":"But that's because people who eat\nfruit and veg and olive oil are freaks --"},{"time":271219,"text":"they're not normal, they're like you;\nthey come to events like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":275067,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":276150,"text":"They're posh, they're wealthy,\nless likely to have outdoor jobs,"},{"time":279193,"text":"less likely to do manual labor,"},{"time":280733,"text":"they have better social support,\nare less likely to smoke;"},{"time":283497,"text":"for a host of fascinating, interlocking"},{"time":285395,"text":"social, political and cultural reasons,"},{"time":287288,"text":"they're less likely to have wrinkles."},{"time":289084,"text":"That doesn't mean\nit's the vegetables or olive oil."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291510,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":292780,"text":"So ideally, what you want\nto do is a trial."},{"time":295297,"text":"People think they're familiar\nwith the idea of a trial."},{"time":297901,"text":"Trials are old; the first one\nwas in the Bible, Daniel 1:12."},{"time":300741,"text":"It's straightforward: take a bunch\nof people, split them in half,"},{"time":303840,"text":"treat one group one way,\nthe other group, the other way."},{"time":306490,"text":"A while later, you see\nwhat happened to each of them."},{"time":309037,"text":"I'm going to tell you about one trial,"},{"time":310895,"text":"which is probably\nthe most well-reported trial"},{"time":313085,"text":"in the UK news media over the past decade."},{"time":315114,"text":"This is the trial of fish oil pills."},{"time":316874,"text":"The claim: fish oil pills improve\nschool performance and behavior"},{"time":320051,"text":"in mainstream children."},{"time":321226,"text":"They said, \"We did a trial."},{"time":322544,"text":"All the previous ones were positive,\nthis one will be too.\""},{"time":325340,"text":"That should ring alarm bells:"},{"time":326746,"text":"if you know the answer to your trial,\nyou shouldn't be doing one."},{"time":329830,"text":"Either you've rigged it by design,"},{"time":331482,"text":"or you've got enough data so there's\nno need to randomize people anymore."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334943,"text":"So this is what they were going\nto do in their trial:"},{"time":337468,"text":"They were taking 3,000 children,"},{"time":339569,"text":"they were going to give them these huge\nfish oil pills, six of them a day,"},{"time":343247,"text":"and then, a year later, measure\ntheir school exam performance"},{"time":346384,"text":"and compare their performance"},{"time":348182,"text":"against what they predicted\ntheir exam performance would have been"},{"time":351362,"text":"if they hadn't had the pills."},{"time":353462,"text":"Now, can anybody spot\na flaw in this design?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":356293,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":357332,"text":"And no professors\nof clinical trial methodology"},{"time":359599,"text":"are allowed to answer this question."},{"time":361349,"text":"So there's no control group."},{"time":363374,"text":"But that sounds really techie, right?\nThat's a technical term."},{"time":366733,"text":"The kids got the pills,\nand their performance improved."}]},{"cues":[{"time":369390,"text":"What else could it possibly\nbe if it wasn't the pills?"},{"time":372868,"text":"They got older; we all develop over time."},{"time":375165,"text":"And of course, there's the placebo effect,"},{"time":377354,"text":"one of the most fascinating things\nin the whole of medicine."},{"time":380216,"text":"It's not just taking a pill\nand performance or pain improving;"},{"time":383153,"text":"it's about our beliefs and expectations,\nthe cultural meaning of a treatment."},{"time":386840,"text":"And this has been demonstrated\nin a whole raft of fascinating studies"},{"time":390134,"text":"comparing one kind of placebo\nagainst another."},{"time":392375,"text":"So we know, for example,"},{"time":393557,"text":"that two sugar pills a day\nare a more effective treatment"},{"time":396294,"text":"for gastric ulcers"},{"time":397537,"text":"than one sugar pill."},{"time":398801,"text":"Two sugar pills a day beats one a day."},{"time":400786,"text":"That's an outrageous\nand ridiculous finding, but it's true."},{"time":403585,"text":"We know from three different studies\non three different types of pain"},{"time":406906,"text":"that a saltwater injection\nis a more effective treatment"},{"time":409575,"text":"than a sugar pill, a dummy pill\nwith no medicine in it,"},{"time":412204,"text":"not because the injection or pills\ndo anything physically to the body,"},{"time":415572,"text":"but because an injection feels\nlike a much more dramatic intervention."},{"time":418952,"text":"So we know that our beliefs\nand expectations can be manipulated,"},{"time":422038,"text":"which is why we do trials\nwhere we control against a placebo,"},{"time":426110,"text":"where one half of the people\nget the real treatment,"},{"time":428672,"text":"and the other half get placebo."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430373,"text":"But that's not enough."},{"time":433236,"text":"What I've just shown you are examples"},{"time":435036,"text":"of the very simple\nand straightforward ways"},{"time":437232,"text":"that journalists and food supplement\npill peddlers and naturopaths"},{"time":440519,"text":"can distort evidence\nfor their own purposes."},{"time":443000,"text":"What I find really fascinating"},{"time":445204,"text":"is that the pharmaceutical industry\nuses exactly the same kinds"},{"time":448385,"text":"of tricks and devices,"},{"time":449937,"text":"but slightly more sophisticated\nversions of them,"},{"time":452728,"text":"in order to distort the evidence\nthey give to doctors and patients,"},{"time":455930,"text":"and which we use to make\nvitally important decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":458516,"text":"So firstly, trials against placebo:"},{"time":461073,"text":"everybody thinks a trial\nshould be a comparison"},{"time":463469,"text":"of your new drug against placebo."},{"time":465088,"text":"But in a lot of situations that's wrong;"},{"time":467032,"text":"often, we already have a good treatment\ncurrently available."},{"time":469954,"text":"So we don't want to know\nthat your alternative new treatment"},{"time":472811,"text":"is better than nothing,"},{"time":473986,"text":"but that it's better than the best\navailable treatment we have."},{"time":476978,"text":"And yet, repeatedly, you consistently\nsee people doing trials"},{"time":479875,"text":"still against placebo."},{"time":481205,"text":"And you can get licensed\nto bring your drug to market"},{"time":483736,"text":"with only data showing\nthat it's better than nothing,"},{"time":486259,"text":"which is useless for a doctor like me\ntrying to make a decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":489285,"text":"But that's not the only way\nyou can rig your data."},{"time":491674,"text":"You can also rig your data"},{"time":492946,"text":"by making the thing you compare\nyour new drug against"},{"time":495463,"text":"really rubbish."},{"time":496644,"text":"You can give the competing drug\nin too low a dose,"},{"time":499137,"text":"so people aren't properly treated."},{"time":500794,"text":"You can give the competing drug\nin too high a dose,"},{"time":503215,"text":"so people get side effects."},{"time":504535,"text":"And this is exactly what happened"},{"time":506239,"text":"with antipsychotic medication\nfor schizophrenia."},{"time":508728,"text":"Twenty years ago, a new generation\nof antipsychotic drugs were brought in;"},{"time":512284,"text":"the promise was they would have\nfewer side effects."},{"time":514865,"text":"So people set about doing trials\nof the new drugs against the old drugs."},{"time":518343,"text":"But they gave the old drugs\nin ridiculously high doses:"},{"time":521052,"text":"20 milligrams a day of haloperidol."},{"time":522921,"text":"And it's a foregone conclusion\nif you give a drug at that high a dose,"},{"time":526499,"text":"it will have more side effects,\nand your new drug will look better."}]},{"cues":[{"time":529803,"text":"Ten years ago, history repeated itself,"},{"time":531815,"text":"when risperidone, the first\nof the new-generation antipsychotic drugs,"},{"time":535164,"text":"came off copyright,\nso anybody could make copies."},{"time":537530,"text":"Everybody wanted to show their drug\nwas better than risperidone,"},{"time":540586,"text":"so you see trials comparing\nnew antipsychotic drugs"},{"time":543011,"text":"against risperidone\nat eight milligrams a day."},{"time":545202,"text":"Again, not an insane dose,\nnot an illegal dose,"},{"time":547440,"text":"but very much at the high end of normal."},{"time":549382,"text":"So you're bound to make\nyour new drug look better."},{"time":551923,"text":"And so it's no surprise that overall,"},{"time":554544,"text":"industry-funded trials\nare four times more likely"},{"time":557337,"text":"to give a positive result"},{"time":558690,"text":"than independently sponsored trials."}]},{"cues":[{"time":561729,"text":"But -- and it's a big but --"}]},{"cues":[{"time":564397,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":566942,"text":"it turns out,"},{"time":568247,"text":"when you look at the methods\nused by industry-funded trials,"},{"time":571912,"text":"that they're actually better\nthan independently sponsored trials."},{"time":575622,"text":"And yet, they always manage\nto get the result that they want."},{"time":578538,"text":"So how does this work?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":579712,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":580749,"text":"How can we explain\nthis strange phenomenon?"},{"time":583540,"text":"Well, it turns out that what happens"},{"time":585362,"text":"is the negative data\ngoes missing in action;"},{"time":587619,"text":"it's withheld from doctors and patients."},{"time":589580,"text":"And this is the most important\naspect of the whole story."},{"time":592302,"text":"It's at the top\nof the pyramid of evidence."},{"time":594360,"text":"We need to have all of the data\non a particular treatment"},{"time":597070,"text":"to know whether or not\nit really is effective."},{"time":599254,"text":"There are two different ways you can spot\nwhether some data has gone missing."},{"time":602945,"text":"You can use statistics\nor you can use stories."},{"time":605168,"text":"I prefer statistics,\nso that's what I'll do first."}]},{"cues":[{"time":607581,"text":"This is a funnel plot."},{"time":608927,"text":"A funnel plot is a very clever\nway of spotting"},{"time":611142,"text":"if small negative trials have disappeared,\nhave gone missing in action."},{"time":614531,"text":"This is a graph of all of the trials done\non a particular treatment."},{"time":618033,"text":"As you go up towards the top of the graph,"},{"time":620312,"text":"what you see is each dot is a trial."},{"time":622265,"text":"As you go up, those are bigger trials,\nso they've got less error;"},{"time":625415,"text":"they're less likely to be randomly false\npositives or negatives."},{"time":628585,"text":"So they all cluster together."},{"time":630001,"text":"The big trials are closer\nto the true answer."},{"time":632532,"text":"Then as you go further down at the bottom,"},{"time":634572,"text":"what you can see is, on this side,\nspurious false negatives,"},{"time":637515,"text":"and over on this side,\nspurious false positives."},{"time":639785,"text":"If there is publication bias,"},{"time":641885,"text":"if small negative trials\nhave gone missing in action,"},{"time":644439,"text":"you can see it on one of these graphs."},{"time":646278,"text":"So you see here\nthat the small negative trials"},{"time":648453,"text":"that should be on the bottom left\nhave disappeared."},{"time":650930,"text":"This is a graph demonstrating\nthe presence of publication bias"},{"time":653889,"text":"in studies of publication bias."},{"time":655833,"text":"And I think that's the funniest\nepidemiology joke you will ever hear."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659159,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":660194,"text":"That's how you can prove it statistically."},{"time":662242,"text":"But what about stories?"},{"time":663417,"text":"Well, they're heinous, they really are."},{"time":665356,"text":"This is a drug called reboxetine."},{"time":666969,"text":"This is a drug which I, myself,\nhave prescribed to patients."},{"time":669932,"text":"And I'm a very nerdy doctor."},{"time":671292,"text":"I hope I go out of my way"},{"time":672628,"text":"to try and read and understand\nall the literature."},{"time":675011,"text":"I read the trials on this."},{"time":676343,"text":"They were all positive,\nall well-conducted."},{"time":678634,"text":"I found no flaw."},{"time":679809,"text":"Unfortunately, it turned out,\nthat many of these trials were withheld."},{"time":683414,"text":"In fact, 76 percent of all of the trials\nthat were done on this drug"},{"time":687983,"text":"were withheld from doctors and patients."},{"time":689958,"text":"Now if you think about it,"},{"time":691235,"text":"if I tossed a coin a hundred times,"},{"time":693556,"text":"and I'm allowed to withhold from you\nthe answers half the times,"},{"time":697116,"text":"then I can convince you\nthat I have a coin with two heads."},{"time":701229,"text":"If we remove half of the data,"},{"time":703166,"text":"we can never know what the true\neffect size of these medicines is."}]},{"cues":[{"time":706928,"text":"And this is not an isolated story."},{"time":709023,"text":"Around half of all of the trial data\non antidepressants has been withheld,"},{"time":712841,"text":"but it goes way beyond that."},{"time":714301,"text":"The Nordic Cochrane Group were trying\nto get ahold of the data on that"},{"time":717671,"text":"to bring it all together."},{"time":718890,"text":"The Cochrane Groups are an international\nnonprofit collaboration"},{"time":721933,"text":"that produce systematic reviews"},{"time":723447,"text":"of all of the data\nthat has ever been shown."},{"time":725568,"text":"And they need to have access\nto all of the trial data."},{"time":728126,"text":"But the companies withheld\nthat data from them."},{"time":730593,"text":"So did the European Medicines Agency --"},{"time":732812,"text":"for three years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734422,"text":"This is a problem that is currently\nlacking a solution."},{"time":737478,"text":"And to show how big it goes,\nthis is a drug called Tamiflu,"},{"time":740401,"text":"which governments around the world"},{"time":742087,"text":"have spent billions\nand billions of dollars on."},{"time":744954,"text":"And they spend that money\non the promise that this is a drug"},{"time":747845,"text":"which will reduce the rate\nof complications with flu."},{"time":750841,"text":"We already have the data"},{"time":752016,"text":"showing it reduces the duration\nof your flu by a few hours."},{"time":754834,"text":"But I don't care about that,\ngovernments don't care."},{"time":757312,"text":"I'm sorry if you have the flu,\nI know it's horrible,"},{"time":759790,"text":"but we're not going to spend\nbillions of dollars"},{"time":762058,"text":"trying to reduce the duration\nof your flu symptoms by half a day."},{"time":765244,"text":"We prescribe these drugs."},{"time":766593,"text":"We stockpile them for emergencies"},{"time":768420,"text":"on the understanding they'll reduce\nthe number of complications,"},{"time":771533,"text":"which means pneumonia and death."},{"time":773091,"text":"The infectious diseases Cochrane Group,\nwhich are based in Italy,"},{"time":776574,"text":"has been trying to get\nthe full data in a usable form"},{"time":779775,"text":"out of the drug companies,"},{"time":781067,"text":"so they can make a full decision"},{"time":783182,"text":"about whether this drug\nis effective or not,"},{"time":785303,"text":"and they've not been able\nto get that information."},{"time":788293,"text":"This is undoubtedly\nthe single biggest ethical problem"},{"time":793523,"text":"facing medicine today."},{"time":795944,"text":"We cannot make decisions\nin the absence of all of the information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":802529,"text":"So it's a little bit difficult from there"},{"time":805530,"text":"to spin in some kind\nof positive conclusion."},{"time":809936,"text":"But I would say this:"},{"time":813671,"text":"I think that sunlight"},{"time":816491,"text":"is the best disinfectant."},{"time":818817,"text":"All of these things\nare happening in plain sight,"},{"time":821576,"text":"and they're all protected\nby a force field of tediousness."},{"time":826371,"text":"And I think, with all\nof the problems in science,"},{"time":828802,"text":"one of the best things that we can do"},{"time":830646,"text":"is to lift up the lid,\nfinger around at the mechanics"},{"time":833473,"text":"and peer in."}]},{"cues":[{"time":834776,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":835960,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}